            <div class="faq-a">Significantly &mdash; your spouse&rsquo;s established attending W-2 plus your resident W-2 combine as joint co-borrowers, often dramatically increasing qualifying capacity. Two-MD households (resident + attending spouse, or two attending spouses) commonly qualify for $1M-$2M+ mortgages even with significant combined student loan balances when both spouses are on IDR with documented servicer payments. Both files combine for joint qualifying.</div>
