            <div class="faq-a">Yes &mdash; resident moonlighting W-2 income aggregates with the primary resident W-2 under <a href="https://selling-guide.fanniemae.com/sel/b3-3.1-01/general-income-information" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">B3-3.1-01</a> as continuing employment with 24-month average. Moonlighting requires 2-year history for full qualifying credit. For PGY-3+ residents with 2-year moonlighting track records, this commonly adds $15K-$40K of qualifying income annually.</div>
