            <div class="faq-q">My SAVE plan enrollment has been in limbo with the legal challenges. How does that affect my IDR documentation?</div>
            <div class="faq-a">During SAVE plan administrative pauses or legal flux, borrowers may be temporarily in forbearance or transitioned to other IDR plans (PAYE, IBR, REPAYE). For mortgage qualifying, we work with your current servicer to obtain documentation showing your current IDR enrollment status and most recent monthly payment. If you&rsquo;re in administrative forbearance with $0 payment, that $0 may count under B3-6-05 depending on the underwriter&rsquo;s interpretation. We coordinate the documentation carefully.</div>
